cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.SY 

This paper deals with optimizing the medium access control (MAC) throughput of a White-Fi network, which falls under the category of network optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves modeling and heuristic algorithms, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper deals with protecting TV reception, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
